Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_path_adjust(25.10)                                  set_path_adjust(25.10)

Name
       set_path_adjust - Defines the slack adjustment value for timing paths

Syntax
       set_path_adjust

       [-help]

       <adjust_value>

       [-path_adjust_group <path_adjust_group_name>]

       [-view <string>]

       [-setup | -hold]

       Defines  the  slack  adjustment value for timing paths. The defined ad-
       justment value is added to the slack of a path specified  by  the  path
       adjust  group, referred to by the -path_adjust_group parameter. You can
       specify a path adjust group by using the set_path_adjust_group command.

       If multiple path adjustment values are  applicable  on  the  same  pin,
       which  is  on the path specified by multiple set_path_adjust_group con-
       straints, then the smallest adjustment value will be applied.

       Note: The set_path_adjust command is not allowed to be used inside  the
       SDC constraints file. It is only allowed in the software run script.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <adjust_value>
              Specifies the value of slack adjustment.

       -hold  Specifies to apply the adjust value to early paths.

       -path_adjust_group <path_adjust_group_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of path adjust group that defines the path
              for which the adjustment will be applied.

       -setup Specifies to apply the adjust value to late paths.

              Note: If you do not specify -setup or -hold parameter, the soft-
              ware sets the adjust value to both setup and hold analysis.

       -view <string>
              Specifies a list of analysis views for which adjustment will  be
              applied.

              This parameter accepts multiple views as argument.

Examples
              * The  following commands define the slack adjustment values for
                the specified views:

                set_path_adjust 0.44 -path_adjust_group AG1 -view view1 -hold

                set_path_adjust 0.44 -path_adjust_group AG2 -view view2 -setup

                set_path_adjust 0.44 -path_adjust_group AG3 -view view3

Related Information
              * set_path_adjust_group

              * reset_path_adjust_group

